data.title: House stalemate still holds back choice of a new speaker
data.description: The House stalemate over choosing a new speaker is continuing. Kevin McCarthy is determined to win over enough fellow Republicans. But the same candidates opposing him have been renominated, assuring the blockade remains. Thursday is Day 3 of the standoff between McCarthy and 20 colleagues who are withholding the support the California Republican needs. So far, six roll call votes have failed to elect a speaker. The impasse has left the House unable to fully form and govern. McCarthy's conservative detractors appear intent on waiting him out, as long as it takes.
